06/05/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Speaking on Monday (5 May), Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic said it is essential that the problems of Kosovo be resolved. 
As priorities, he cited resolving the security situation and meeting UNMIK standards, then deciding on the status of the province. 
Zivkovic said the Serbian government has succeeded in its policies related to Kosovo and that the international community, represented by UNMIK and KFOR, should contribute to the process. 
(Tanjug, BBC - 05/05/03)
